Place a field object.

Add Widget.
Drag a Field Widget from within “Smart Dashboard” to the grid.

We push our Robot Pose2D at “SmartDashboard/Field/Robot”, which might affect how Elastic processes our Network Tables traffic. It looks like you’re sending yours at “SentField/Robot” which might be the issue.

Try renaming “SentField” to just “Field” and see if that makes it work. If not, then make it “SmartDashboard/Field”

But Elastic shows it as a Field object just fine:

image787×486 44.3 KB

See if you can load this config file into your Elastic (File:Open Layout) and see a Field, ideally with your bot on it:
elastic-layout-for-10903.json (9.5 KB)

I’m running Elastic 2025.1.0 if that matters.

MaxedPC:

We are on a fresh install of elastic and everything - our code is here.

I checked the code, and assuming you’re dragging out the SmartDashboard/SentField table, it should display properly. In the picture you sent it looks like you’re dragging out SmartDashboard/Field instead.

Unrelated to this, but a fresh install of Elastic won’t make a difference here since the configuration for widget placement is stored on the local machine and persists across restarts.
